const e='---\ntitle: "Authentication"\ndescription: "Learn how to authenticate your API requests"\n---\n\n# Authentication\n\nWhen you purchase a `dynamic_api` (Dynamic API Quota Sales) type product in APayShop, the system will automatically generate an exclusive API Key for you. You need to use this Key to call the corresponding service interfaces.\n\n## Authentication Method\n\nAPayShop uses the standard HTTP `Authorization` header for authentication. When sending API requests, please include your API Key as a Bearer Token in the request header.\n\n### Format Requirements\n\nHeader Name: `Authorization`\nHeader Value: `Bearer YOUR_API_KEY`\n\n### Example Request\n\nBelow is an example of sending an authenticated request using cURL:\n\n```bash\ncurl -X GET https://yourdomain.com/api/v1/some-service \\\n  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk_test_1234567890abcdef" \\\n  -H "Content-Type: application/json"\n```\n\n## How to get an API Key?\n\n1. Purchase a `dynamic_api` type product in the storefront and complete the payment.\n2. After successful payment, go to the **"Order History"** page.\n3. Click on the details of the corresponding order, and you will directly see the API Key allocated to you by the system and the available quota in the Fulfillment Result area.\n\n> **⚠️ Security Warning**\n> \n> Please keep your API Key as safe as a password. **Absolutely never** hardcode it in client-side code (such as browser-side JS, mobile Apps), and do not commit it to public GitHub repositories. If your key is leaked, please contact the administrator immediately to invalidate it in the backend and generate a new one.\n\n## Quota Consumption Mechanism\n\nEvery time you successfully call a billing interface using a valid API Key, the system will automatically deduct the corresponding value from your available quota.\nWhen the quota is exhausted, the API will refuse service and return a `402 Payment Required` or `403 Forbidden` status code. You can purchase the product again to replenish your quota.\n';export{e as default};
//# sourceMappingURL=2.authentication.mjs.map
